<h1>Documentation and Revitalization Projects</h1>

<h2>Ticha Project</h2>

<p>Since 2013, I have been a research assistant on the <a href="http://ticha.haverford.edu" target="_blank">Ticha Project</a>, a digital text explorer of Colonial Zapotec documents.</p>

<h2>Valley Zapotec Talking Dictionaries</h2>

<p>In 2015-2016, as part of the Linguistics Field School (NSF REU Site Grant #1461056) in Oaxaca, I helped build <a href="http://talkingdictionary.swarthmore.edu/zapotecs/" target="_blank">Talking Dictionaries</a> for three Valley Zapotec languages.</p> 

<h2>Indigenous Languge Engagement on Twitter</h2>

<p>I actively engage with indigenous languages on Twitter (<a href="https://twitter.com/mayhplumb" target="_blank">&#64;mayhplumb</a>).  In 2016 and 2017 I participated in the Voces del Valle Project to encourage indigenous language speakers to write on Twitter (see <a href="https://twitter.com/search?f=tweets&vertical=default&q=%23UsaTuVoz&src=tyah" target="_blank">#UsaTuVoz</a>).</p>

